On National Energy Assistance Day, the White House is coordinating outreach efforts to encourage American families to enroll in assistance programs that can help with home energy costs. The Biden-Harris Administration has provided record funding for the Low Income Home Energy Assistance Program (LIHEAP) this year, and the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law includes funds to reduce home energy costs. The White House is urging states to utilize all available resources from the American Rescue Plan and the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law for energy assistance. The Administration has also announced that households in need can find resources in their area at EnergyHelp.us or by calling the National Energy Assistance Referral hotline. The article also mentions HHS LIHEAP Funding Awards that may be used in FY 2022.